                  CHAP. II.
                  What soile and aire the vine doth most delight in.
                  
                     THe vine groweth not but in certaine places that are fit and naturall for it,Two things to be considered in the planting of vines.
which is a thing to be accounted of by vs, so much the more excellent,
because the speciall propertie of this plant is more commended by men
than any other, in respect of the good it ministreth, which i
